  "name": "Casterbane Shot",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/spells/rock-royal-1.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Life in the Mana Wastes, where magic has unpredictable and often fatal effects, has taught you to disable spellcasters with your firearms.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Amateur Gunslinger or the grit class feature, Point-Blank Shot, Precise Shot, base attack bonus +4.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>If you ready a ranged attack with a firearm to attack a spellcaster when he begins casting a spell and successfully hit your opponent, you can expend 1 grit point to increase the target's concentration check DC for being injured while casting by 5.<br/><br/><b>Combat Trick</b><br/>When using Casterbane Shot, you can spend up to 5 stamina points to increase the DC of the concentration check imposed by the feat by an amount equal to the number of stamina points spent.",
